explanation:
Agent A is correct. In the supplied project configuration OS_DEBUG is defined as an empty replacement, so the statement
    OS_DEBUG("listen: %s\n", strerror(errno));
preprocessor-expands to an empty statement (a null statement). That null statement is executed at runtime (control reaches it in the error path) but performs no operation and its removal would not change program behaviour — which fits MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2’s definition of dead code. (If OS_DEBUG were defined to perform logging in some other build configuration then the statement would not be dead in that configuration, but MISRA Rule 2.2 applies to the project as built; with the provided definitions it is dead code.)
